{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Two horses were trottin'  they pranced and they [F]ran
Each one was co[C]mmanded  by a cavalry [G7]man
Two horses stood [C]grazin’  where their dead riders [F]lay
A Union [C]Mare  [G7]and a Confederate [C]Grey
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
They nuzzled each other  as they teased and had [F]fun
They bathed in the [C]warm rays  of the old southern [G7]sun
No more senseless [C]orders  for them to [F]obey
So they acted like [C]lovers  [G7]this mare and this [C]grey
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Now these are such sad times  that were all livin' [F]in
For killin' your [C]brother  is the mightiest [G7]sin
How happy we’d [C]be  if we acted the [F]way 
Of The Union [C]Mare  [G7]and the Confederate [C]Grey
{end_of_verse}

